DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Gastrin Level Outcome Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The numeric laboratory value, in picogram/milliliter(pg/nL), per the test performed for the level of Gastrin (101 aa, ~11 kDa) encoded by the human GAST gene. This protein plays a role in the modulation of food digestion by the gastrointestinal system.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Information related to the laboratory result in level of Gastrin (101 aa, ~11 kDa) is encoded by the human GAST gene. This protein plays a role in the modulation of food digestion by the gastrointestinal system.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

ValueDomain.preferredName: Laboratory Test Result Picogram Per Milliliter Value
ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: The laboratory result in picogram per milliliter(pg/mL) value.  A milligram is approximately 450,000 times smaller than a pound and 28,000 times smaller than an ounce. The metric unit of mass equal to one trillionth of a gram (10E-12 gram).  A unit of volume equal to one millionth (10E-6) of a cubic meter, one thousandth of a liter, one cubic centimeter, or 0.061023 7 cubic inch. A cubic centimeter is the CGS unit of volume.
